慰安妇是在军队妓院中称呼妓女的委婉语，并特指二战期间大日本帝国军队所奴役的妓女形式。<ref>{{Citation|url=http://japanfocus.org/products/details/2373|title=Japan’s ‘Comfort Women’: It's time for the truth (in the ordinary, everyday sense of the word)|author=Tessa Morris-Suzuki|date=2007-03-08|accessdate=2008-12-15|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090109083324/http://japanfocus.org/products/details/2373|archivedate=2009年1月9日}}</ref><ref name="definition">{{Harvnb|WCCW|2004}}.</ref>

慰安妇人数约为200,000人，经过日本学者校对后最低人数为20,000人，<ref name="AWF_CW">{{Harvnb|Asian Women'sFund|p=10|Ref=AWF-CW}}.</ref>中国学者估算最多为410,000人。<ref>{{Harvnb|Rose|2005|p=[http://books.google.com/books?id=W2nU1Xu0XdkC&pg=PA88 88]}}.</ref>最终人数依然在研究和讨论当中。历史学家和研究者认定大多数慰安妇来自朝鲜、中国、日本和菲律宾<ref>{{Cite web|title=Women and World War II - Comfort Women|url=http://womenshistory.about.com/od/warwwii/a/comfort_women.htm|access-date=2014-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303165814/http://womenshistory.about.com/od/warwwii/a/comfort_women.htm|archive-date=2016-03-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，但也有来自泰国、越南、马来西亚、台湾、印尼、东帝汶<ref>{{Cite web|title=Japanese Military Sexual Slavery in East Timor|url=http://www.etan.org/issues/ww2.htm|access-date=2014-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140127012802/http://www.etan.org/issues/ww2.htm|archive-date=2014-01-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>和其它日军占领地的妇女。[[慰安所|慰安所]]地点位于日本、中国、菲律宾、印尼、英属马来亚、泰国、缅甸、新几内亚、香港、澳门和法属印度尼西亚。<ref>{{Harvnb|Reuters|2007-03-05}}.</ref>

在日军占领地中，年轻妇女常被拐走。有时，妇女被军队招去工作。<ref>{{Harvnb|Yoshimi|2000|pp=100–101, 105–106, 110–111}};<br />{{Harvnb|Fackler|2007-03-06|Ref=CITEREFNY Times2007-03-06}};<br />{{Harvnb|BBC|2007-03-02}};<br />{{Harvnb|BBC|2007-03-08}}.</ref>日军资料自己记录着用暴力手段掳掠妇女的行径。<ref>{{Harvnb|van Buitenlandse zaken|1994|pp=6–9, 11, 13–14}}.</ref>然而，日本历史学家[[秦郁彦|秦郁彦]]称日本军队和政府没有组织强征慰安妇的事件。<ref>{{Citation|url=http://hassin.sejp.net/Hata-Ianfu_text.pdf|title=NO ORGANIZED OR FORCED RECRUITMENT: MISCONCEPTIONS ABOUT COMFORT WOMEN AND THE JAPANESE MILITARY|author=Hata Ikuhiko|publisher=hassin.sejp.net|format=PDF|accessdate=2008-12-15|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080904020445/http://hassin.sejp.net/Hata-Ianfu_text.pdf|archivedate=2008-09-04}} (First published in Shokun May, 2007 issue in Japanese. Translated by Society for the Dissemination of Historical Fact).</ref>

二战日军慰安妇的人数的本质依然在争议当中，在日本和其它远东国家都是高度政治化的话题。<ref>According to journalist Satoshi Ikeuchi : "Even though the forcible recruitment of women was not systematically implemented, the (Japanese) government should acknowledge its moral responsibility if any single woman victimized by the private operators through fraud, exploitation, violence or other acts of intimidation comes forward to tell her story. The government should do so because the military gave consent to set up brothels for soldiers and had responsibility for overseeing them.»  «In this context, the issue of the so-called comfort women was invested with extreme importance as the epitome of Japanese sin from the viewpoint of some and became the focal point of contention, The excessive effort by leftists and liberals in politicizing this issue as one of the few means left to shake conservative dominance, by extending the notion of coercion to the extreme, resulted in alienating a large part of the nation. Their open intention to collude with rising tides of hostile nationalism in Korea and China also hardened the minds of many in Japan." April 25, 2007. Satoshi Ikeuchi, [http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/dy/columns/commentary/20070425dy01.htm Overcoming postwar mind-set] {{Wayback|url=http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/dy/columns/commentary/20070425dy01.htm|date=20121205130201}}, Daily Yomuri Online, April 25, 2007.</ref>

许多军队妓院由私人建立而成，受到朝鲜军警的监视。有的日本历史学家利用前慰安妇的证词辩称帝国军队没有直接参与恐吓、胁迫、拐骗的行动中来，在日军占领地有时会有拐卖妇女儿童的事情出现。<ref name="denial">{{Harvnb|Onishi|2007-03-08|Ref=CITEREFNY Times2007-03-08}}.</ref>

